PROGRAM OVERVIEW

NEXUS 220-XYZ is a conceptual multidisciplinary engineering research
platform developed by Parallel Industries 220 (PI220) to investigate
controlled atmospheric electrical-discharge phenomena within a modular,
instrumented laboratory environment.

The architecture is organized around a Central Engineering and Energy
Core surrounded by distributed atmospheric engineering chambers. The
platform emphasizes systems engineering, repeatable experimentation,
digital engineering, maintainability and lifecycle optimization.

The objective is to provide a flexible research infrastructure for
studying atmospheric conditions, environmental control, electrical
measurements and future energy-related engineering concepts.

